<p>â€œBut what?â€ She crossed her arms over her chest.</p>

<p>â€œWell,â€ he said. â€œThey â€¦ Theyâ€™reÂ bugs.â€</p>

<p>She walked over to the sink and turned on both faucets, the hot and the cold. She watched the water pour out, over the sudsy dishes.Â </p>

<p>â€œFor your information,â€ she said, snatching a spoon out of a mug, and holding a spoon up to the light, â€œtheyâ€™re mollusks, not bugs.â€</p>

