<p>â€œWipe that smirk off your face,â€ says Cordelia.</p>

<p>I say nothing.</p>

<p>â€œCrash!â€ says Cordelia. â€œOnly three left.â€</p>

<p>Nobody ever says what will happen if all the stacks of plates fall down.</p>

<p>Hereâ€™s some advice from novelist, Chuck Palahniukâ€
In six seconds, youâ€™ll hate me.</p>

<p>But in six months, youâ€™ll be a better writer.</p>

<p>From this point forward â€“ at least for the next half year â€“ you may not use â€œthoughtâ€ verbs. These include: Thinks, Knows, Understands, Realizes, Believes, Wants, Remembers, Imagines, Desires, and a hundred others you love to use.</p>

<p>The list should also include: Loves and Hates.</p>

<p>And it should include: Is and Has, but weâ€™ll get to those, later.</p>

<p>Until some time around Christmas, you canâ€™t write: Kenny wondered if Monica didnâ€™t like him going out at nightâ€¦â€</p>

